        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:06PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 605 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Manhattan, or 17 miles west of Bozeman, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bozeman, Belgrade, Manhattan, Logan, Maudlow, Four Corners,
Amsterdam, Bozeman Hot Springs, Church Hill, Gallatin Gateway, and
Menard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
